# @param {String} s
# @param {Integer} k
# @return {Integer}
def minimum_changes(s, k)
    n = s.length
    dp = Array.new(k+1) { Array.new(n+1) { Float::INFINITY } }
    dp[0][0] = 0

    # Precompute the cost to make each substring a palindrome
    cost = Array.new(n) { Array.new(n, 0) }
    (0...n).each do |i|
        (i...n).each do |j|
            cost[i][j] = compute_cost(s, i, j)
        end
    end

    (1..k).each do |i|
        (1..n).each do |j|
            (i-1...j).each do |m|
                dp[i][j] = [dp[i][j], dp[i-1][m] + cost[m][j-1]].min
            end
        end
    end

    dp[k][n]
end

def compute_cost(s, i, j)
    changes = 0
    while i < j
        changes += 1 if s[i] != s[j]
        i += 1
        j -= 1
    end
    changes
end
